	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A few other things that may be of help that you likely already know.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you have two or three mobs that have aggroed, unless your tank is very low on life, wait for one mob to go down.  Taking hits from one mob is MUCH easier than taking hits from two mobs.  Also, make ABSOLUTELY sure that the groups you are in have suitable tanks.  Although some people think that shamans, other clerics, and even druids (yes there are some out there) can tank, don't believe this.  Druids kite, as to shamans to some degree.  A good druid or shaman never gets hit when soloing, whereas when clerics solo, they get hit unless their root sticks.<br>A not on soloing now:  I have done this a little when I have not been able to get into any groups.  The four most important spells to me for successful cleric soloing are your highest level damage spell (for me Wrath), your highest root (Enstill), your highest stun (Holy Wrath), and divine aura/barrier.  ALWAYS have your first cast be either root or stun.  I pull with root because it appears to me that it is less resisted than stuns.  After the mob is rooted, cast your DD spell.  Then, cast your stun spell.  This system has kept mobs from rushing me several times, as it has been stunned just as the root wore off.  You will also notice that some DD spells and all stuns have a recast time on them.  Dont panic if neither of your spells have repopped, just cast root again if mana permits.  And finally, and this comment holds true in all situations and was stated in the second post...ALWAYS HAVE DIVINE AURA UP.  It takes 10 mana, and has a casting time of 1, making it a necessity when you run out of mana and/or are trying to evade an attacker.  This has saved my life many times.  It has also been a source of much frustration, as I have cast it and been 10 feet from the zone and been stunned.  Invulnerability wore off...LOADING PLEASE WAIT...<br>Not a pretty picture, but still, it will save your life so many times.  The key is to know when to cast it, and to know your tanks.<br><br>Korrd Kegtapper<br>Level 31 Cleric of Bristlebane<br>Tunare Server =)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
